GUI error message when sim fails due to pop creation failing to produce pwop within Nb tolerance

Thu Apr 20 16:56:56 MDT 2017
To reduce IO costs, especially for long simuilations with many cycles, the simulation output 
should be written directly to a genepop.  I see no reason to date to retain any of the other 
files currently output (and from which the genepop file is constructed after they have been written).
I think a good strategy would be to write the data to data struct like a class, and every N cycles
update a genepop output file.

