Thu Jul 20 14:34:47 MDT 2017
1. In the current Nb estimation logic, for schemes "cohorts" and "individual
   criteria", the paramters min and max pop indiv totals, are tested after the
   sampling (i.e. tested using total chort individuals sampled) and, if the
   sample is out of range [min,max] an error is thrown and the estimation is
   aborted.  We should simply skip the pop and write a message to *msgs output, 
   and proceed to the next pop.
